<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="5">Late in the night when [I] appear at the gate, </l>
<l corresp="4">praising according to custom, my instruments sounding </l>
<l corresp="3">that looked like, in the middle of the sea, </l>
<l corresp="1">the white moon in the sky </l>
<l corresp="2">when the order of three [times] five [days] was completed, </l>
<l corresp="6">although many slept he does not sleep, </l>
<l corresp="8ab">my father who has heard </l>
<l corresp="7">…………… high who guards the world, </l>
<l corresp="9ab">and when understanding what he heard, </l>
<l corresp="8cd">	[namely] the very voice of my Kiṇai drum, </l>
<l corresp="9cd">	[his] zeal unabated, </l>
<l corresp="10">he removes from [my] sides the rags turned old, </l>
<l corresp="11">distinction of very great excellence……… </l>
<l corresp="12">……………………………………………. </l>
<l corresp="13">provides a Kaliṅkam cloth, looked at my waist, </l>
<l corresp="14">[and] sways in day[-fresh] intoxication from fibre-filtered toddy. </l>
<l corresp="15">Although I, who do not know the time, was familiar with the abode, </l>
<l corresp="16a-c">apart from chasing away his own enemies, </l>
<l corresp="16d-17">is he not capable of chasing away the enemy hunger from those who join [him]? </l>
<l corresp="18">……………. that abounded in brave men, </l>
<l corresp="19">at poles for sacrifices that abound in Vedic learning, </l>
<l corresp="20ab">…. where descend into the dark backwaters </l>
<l corresp="23">the lord of fertile ..., pleasing to stay in </l>
<l>a good town where bustling ships are moored at every harbour, (22+20d)</l>
<l corresp="21">being sent sweepingly along the river to the expanse of the clear water. </l>
</lg>
